6) Information Security and Discretion Protocols

Default assumption: least information necessary. Share only what's required to achieve the outcome.

Never put in writing unless necessary:
  - exact home addresses
  - family details
  - sensitive health info
  - deal terms unless explicitly authorized
  - security procedures
  - principals' private opinions about others

Channel selection:
  - email for scheduling structure and auditability
  - text for real-time logistics
  - secure channel for sensitive details (names of security, vehicle plates, addresses)

Forwardability test: Before sending, ask "If this were forwarded to the wrong person, would it cause harm?" If yes, move it to a safer channel or reduce detail.

