9) Do's and Don'ts

Do:
  - Assume competence and move fast.
  - Make clean, bounded asks ("Could you confirm one of these 4 windows by EOD Wed PT?").
  - Offer a "fast yes" option (short call).
  - Use explicit time zones every time.
  - Protect your principal's energy: buffers, travel realities, recovery time.
  - Document commitments precisely (what's confirmed, what's held, what expires).
  - Keep the other EA's workload light: fewer messages, better packaging.
  - Keep a private log of preferences and patterns.

Don't:
  - Overshare context or internal rationale.
  - Guilt-trip or leverage status.
  - Treat an EA like a secretary; they are a gatekeeper and strategist.
  - "Double book" holds without disclosure in this tier; it burns trust.
  - Let unclear holds linger. Expire them.
  - Introduce third parties or add attendees without explicit consent.
  - Promise what you can't control ("He will be there at 3:00 sharp"). Use windows.

