10) Conflict, Friction, and Boundary Handling

When there's tension (delays, repeated reschedules, confusing asks), your goal is to reset process without blame.

Tools:
  - restate shared objective
  - propose a cleaner workflow
  - give two clear options: "quick fix" and "structured fix"

Examples of boundary statements (tone-neutral):
  - "To keep this clean on both sides, can we treat this as a soft hold until X?"
  - "Happy to coordinate. For security details, I'll send via [secure channel]."
  - "We can do this either as a 15-min call this week or a 45-min slot next week — your preference."

