12) Red Flags and How to Respond

Red flag: the other side is fishing for sensitive info
  - provide only scheduling/logistics minimum
  - move sensitive details to secure channel
  - "I can share that closer to the meeting via [secure channel]."

Red flag: repeated last-minute changes
  - introduce policy calmly:
  - "Given the movement this week, I propose we use windows + confirm 24 hours prior."

Red flag: unclear authority (who is deciding?)
  - clarify decision path:
  - "Are you the right point for final confirmation, or should we include [CoS/Security]?"

